<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="211" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,325,710]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,325,350]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Female (
<figureCitation box="[387,469,325,350]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1932,1954]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,774,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,774,1897]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Ptilothyris climacista Meyrick. A, Holotype, female, in NHMUK; B, Labels of holotype; C, Red-tagged specimen; D, Labels of the red-tagged specimen; E, Specimens placed under the name of P. climacista Meyrick in NHMUK; E-1, Specimen misidentified as P. climacista Meyrick." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594871/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Figs. 6</figureCitation>
A–E). Forewing length 9.0 mm. The wing pattern of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick. A" authorityYear="1926" box="[1106,1254,325,350]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Ptilothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="climacista">
<emphasis box="[1106,1254,325,350]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">P. climacista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham" authorityName="Walsingham. A" authorityYear="1897" box="[264,540,361,386]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Ptilothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="purpurea">
<emphasis box="[264,394,362,385]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">P. purpurea</emphasis>
Walsingham
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authority="Ghesquiere" authorityName="Ghesquiere. A" authorityYear="1940" box="[578,857,361,386]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Ptilothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="porphyrea">
<emphasis box="[578,721,361,386]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">P. porphyrea</emphasis>
Ghesquière
</taxonomicName>
, but it can be distinguished by having a semi-ovate, pale orange patch on the forewing, and the hind wing with a similar semi-transparent patch as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyrick" authorityName="Meyr., E. Meyrick" authorityYear="1932" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Ptilothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serangota">
<emphasis box="[1293,1436,398,421]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">P. serangota</emphasis>
Meyrick
</taxonomicName>
, but the color is pale orange, not white. The species was described based on a single female.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
