<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="212" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Remarks.</emphasis>
In NHMUK, five more specimens, except one specimen (
<figureCitation box="[1049,1125,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1932,1954]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,774,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,774,1897]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Ptilothyris climacista Meyrick. A, Holotype, female, in NHMUK; B, Labels of holotype; C, Red-tagged specimen; D, Labels of the red-tagged specimen; E, Specimens placed under the name of P. climacista Meyrick in NHMUK; E-1, Specimen misidentified as P. climacista Meyrick." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594871/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
E-1) which is certainly a misidentification of 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyrick" authorityName="Meyr., E. Meyrick" authorityYear="1932" box="[381,629,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Ptilothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serangota">
<emphasis box="[381,522,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">P. serangota</emphasis>
Meyrick
</taxonomicName>
, are placed under the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyr" authorityName="Meyrick. A" authorityYear="1926" box="[951,1262,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Ptilothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="climacista">
<emphasis box="[951,1193,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Ptilothyris climacista</emphasis>
Meyr
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1279,1368,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1932,1954]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,774,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,774,1897]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Ptilothyris climacista Meyrick. A, Holotype, female, in NHMUK; B, Labels of holotype; C, Red-tagged specimen; D, Labels of the red-tagged specimen; E, Specimens placed under the name of P. climacista Meyrick in NHMUK; E-1, Specimen misidentified as P. climacista Meyrick." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594871/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
). One specimen (
<figureCitation box="[274,363,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1932,1954]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,774,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,774,1897]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Ptilothyris climacista Meyrick. A, Holotype, female, in NHMUK; B, Labels of holotype; C, Red-tagged specimen; D, Labels of the red-tagged specimen; E, Specimens placed under the name of P. climacista Meyrick in NHMUK; E-1, Specimen misidentified as P. climacista Meyrick." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594871/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
) of this series bearing a red tag has four labels (
<figureCitation box="[926,1015,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1932,1954]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,774,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,774,1897]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Ptilothyris climacista Meyrick. A, Holotype, female, in NHMUK; B, Labels of holotype; C, Red-tagged specimen; D, Labels of the red-tagged specimen; E, Specimens placed under the name of P. climacista Meyrick in NHMUK; E-1, Specimen misidentified as P. climacista Meyrick." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594871/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
) as “Afriq. Occid. Johann-Albrechts Höhe Station-Kamerun, L. Conradt, 1896”, “Paravicini Coll. B. M. 1937-383”, “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyr., M" authorityName="Meyr., M" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Ptilothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="climacista">
<emphasis box="[1105,1351,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Ptilothyris climacista</emphasis>
Meyr., M
</taxonomicName>
456-157”. Although a red label or tag usually indicates a 
<typeStatus box="[868,969,295,320]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">holotype</typeStatus>
, it is confirmed that the 
<typeStatus box="[1270,1368,295,320]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyrick" authorityName="Meyrick. A" authorityYear="1926" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Ptilothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="climacista">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">P. climacista</emphasis>
Meyrick
</taxonomicName>
is certainly the specimen in 
<figureCitation box="[697,788,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1932,1954]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,774,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,774,1897]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Ptilothyris climacista Meyrick. A, Holotype, female, in NHMUK; B, Labels of holotype; C, Red-tagged specimen; D, Labels of the red-tagged specimen; E, Specimens placed under the name of P. climacista Meyrick in NHMUK; E-1, Specimen misidentified as P. climacista Meyrick." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594871/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
. It is unfortunate that assigning the rest to this species or even to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1897" box="[352,470,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Ptilothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[352,470,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Ptilothyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could not be done without examining the male genitalia. A further study is needed for the generic placement of this species.
</paragraph>
